caption: You can't go wrong with that glass of Asahi beer and the delicious food! It's a must-go location to chill and relax with friends and loveones.

If you’re looking for amazing Kushikatsu in Honolulu, this is it! The batter is extremely light and the skewers are all seasoned and fried perfectly. To top it all off, the staff if extremely friendly and attentive. Make sure to call ahead for reservations as this place keeps busy.

Absolutely delicious.  Specializes in kusi-katsu, a form of breaded frying, but has sushi and sashimi, and many other dishes as well.  Bar has house wine, sake, shochu, two whiskeys, one tequila, and beer. Make reservations as it gets busy.

Wonderful food, atmosphere very warm, cozy.   Staff very friendly,  warm, speedy,  and genuine.   A couple from Japan  (he's chef,  she's dining room service) own the restaurant,  and additional service help in kitchen and in dining room work in total harmony to create a very fun,  relaxing,  tasty experience.
ONOLICIOUS FOOD, GOOD DRINKS

Who doesn't love fried things on sticks? All the items are lightly battered and fried, but not that heavy, oily American fried. Lots of variety for sticks and then there are other izakaya items to round out the meal. Prices on alcohol were reasonable. The lemon chuhi was a little weak but we just switched to straight shochu anyway afterward. Get the chicken wing -- crispy on the outside and moist on the inside. Tamago was also excellent.
Scallops, shrimp, lotus root, quail eggs
Best Kushi Katsu I've had since our trip to Japan. The Yuzu Sorbet was a perfect finish too!

We went there last night for my niece's bday. First time for all 7 of us, we had a res for 7p and were seated right away.  Food was good, lots of selection. Service was okay, had to remind them of our order and drinks too many times. Kinda irahz.  We got lucky on the parking, several stalls were available in the lot.

I should say it is not your typical Japanese restaurant but the food was delicious price a little high but totally worth it the thing that in really impressed me was to service it was superb really superb I was really impressed when I first went in and the greeting we received I was really impressed totally recommend this restaurant

I like to sit at the counter so I can see the Chef make all kinds of different Kushi Katsu (katsu on stix). The food varies also from curry to ramen. I recommend getting ebi (shrimp) with side order curry on side, the combo is delicious, another alternate is the croquette with curry.  The atmosphere is casual. Parking is free.  Oh and by the way. All the stuff in this restaurant goes well with beer. ENJOY!!!!

For the katsu we ordered the salmon, ahi, beef, onion, takoyaki, mountain yam, octopus, chicken, croquet, and bacon. They were pretty good. I liked the yam, onion, and octopus more. We also had the beef tataki - which was a bit undercooked and/or underseasoned for me. The jellyfish was also yummy (maybe just a tad bit too salty). The servers were also really friendly and welcoming!

The prices can get crazy if you go nuts but there are plenty of options to keep things reasonable and within a budget. I didn't think any of the seafood was great but all the veggies had a great taste. Parking is terrible but after being on island long enough you get used to it. A must try if anything.
Staff is very friendly and the food definitely hours the spot when you're craving for something fried.  The Twinkie is a must
Great Japanese food

Japanese Kushiage Izakaya. KUSHIAGE means a Japanese dish of deep-fried skewered meat and vegetables. You should try! It's great food, great service, great sake! love it! Try "Cheese Kushiage" with salt.

Now this is a place you wanna go to when you wanna get you fry on. My all time favs were the cheese and the pork belly. I thought the cheese would be mozzarella but it was cheddar. The deep fried coating was light and not too greasy. I'm not sure what kind of oil they were using but it was great because it had no after taste.  Now I love fried food but you can only eat so much of it. I thought I would have room for the chix wing (did you see the pic?) But I was too full and I could feel my coronary arteries starting to harden. There was really no respite in the menu. A little side of mac salad would have evened out my palate but all they had was green salads, tofu, fried potatoes with cream cheese sauce, and edamame.  This is the kind of place you wash down grease with beer.  The atmosphere was friendly and the chef and apprentice were nice.  FYI: Parking lot is small and shared with other businesses. Sometimes there is an attendant during the evening hours but if not then you would have to surrender to street parking which might be a bit tricky around this neighborhood

(Translated by Google) A skewer cutlery that has already captured the local heart. Since the style is Kanto, those who are used to the Kansai style should be prepared. Lively, friendly, honest staff. The menu is also nice. Favor and respect for deep-fried foods that take into account the texture of the ingredients, rather than the general Hawaiian “KATSU”. Cocktails are extremely thin, so if you can't drink, you should have a soft drink. If you can make a reservation, ◎  (Original) 既にローカルの心をつかんで離さない串カツ屋。 スタイルは関東なので、関西風に慣れてる人はちゃんと心構えを。 活気があって愛想がよく、実直なスタッフ。メニューもいい感じ。 衣ばっかりの一般的なハワイの"KATSU"ではなく、具との食感をちゃんと考慮された揚げものに好感と尊敬。カクテルは極薄なので、お酒飲めない人は素直にソフトドリンクを。できれば予約した方が◎

Take this review with a grain of salt since your experience may differ.  - They are still in the soft opening phase and training new employees. One worker just started today. - Make RESERVATIONS especially for dinner time.  EXPERIENCE: When we arrived and they asked us if we had reservations which we didn't they said that they could seat us as long as we were finished before a certain time. We thought this was fine but after waiting 30+ minutes and our food didn't come I was starting to get worried (yes, I know how long it was because I could see from when I checked in just to make sure how long the wait was). Also a lot of the back menu was covered with stickers saying 'coming soon' over the items not yet available. They think it will be another month before the grand opening.  FOOD: Some stuff like the Mushrooms & Oysters were really good, while the Tako was okay (my wife said it had a slight fishy taste).  OVERALL: So if you have a reservation and not in a rush it's not that bad.
